.Im MicroEmacs modes
.so me.tni
.TH hide 2m
.XI hide - "Hide buffer"
.SH NAME
hide \- Hide buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "hide Mode"
.sp
\fBH\fR \- mode line letter.
.SH DESCRIPTION
This  mode  can  only be set on a  buffer  and  when  enabled  the  buffer  is
effectively  hidden  from the user. When set the buffer is hidden  from the buffer
completion list used by commands such as
.Ht find-buffer 2 ,
the buffer is also ignored by commands
.Ht list-buffers 2 ,
.Ht save-some-buffers 2
and
.Ht delete-some-buffers 2 .
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Hl "Operating Modes" Modes - ,
.Ht find-buffer 2 ,
.Ht list-buffers 2 .
.ad
